    <h1>Red&#xAD;dit</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20201215/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-12-15"><time>2020-12-15</time></a>
        - <span>BUSINESS</span>
        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>So­cial net­work firm Red­dit said on Sun­day that it would buy short-video plat­form Dub­s­mash, be­com­ing the lat­est com­pany to ex­pand in a space dom­i­nated by Chi­nese-owned Tik­Tok.</p>
    <p>The fi­nan­cial terms of the deal were not dis­closed, but a spokesman for Red­dit said the ac­qui­si­tion was based on a com­bi­na­tion of cash and stock.</p>
    <p>Red­dit said in a blog post that the deal would give its users, who can al­ready up­load and stream videos, ac­cess to Dub­s­mash’s edit­ing and short-video cre­ation tools.</p>


